  "prompt": "What is the meaning of the phrase - 'majboori ka naam mahatma gandhi'?",
  "response": "The phrase \"majboori ka naam Mahatma Gandhi\" is a Hindi expression that translates to \"the name of compulsion is Mahatma Gandhi.\" It is often used to convey the idea that in situations of necessity or compulsion, people may have to resort to unconventional or unexpected measures. The phrase suggests that even figures like Mahatma Gandhi, known for their principles of non-violence and moral leadership, might be invoked or referenced in the context of difficult choices or situations when people feel compelled to act.\n\nIn a broader sense, it can reflect on the struggles and choices individuals face in challenging circumstances, illustrating how moral and ethical considerations can become intertwined with the pressures of reality.",
